This paper discusses the design and evaluation of a benchmark for Object-Oriented Databases (OODBs), which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the implementation of the benchmark in two different OODBs, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The evaluation of a specific clustering policy also involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
